oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Southeastern Express Railway Depot
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Street scene showing the Southeastern Express Railway Depot, located off of Main Street. There are people waiting by the railroad tracks.

John Roper Branner (1822-1869) gave the right-of-way through his property in addition to three acres of land upon which to build the railroad station. This arrangement stipulated that every passenger train stop at Mossy Creek. Branner later became the president of the line, which is now a part of the Southern Railway System.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
